# Tasks

The canonical work-tracking system for {{PROJECT_NAME}}.

## Lifecycle

Directories: {{TASK_DIRS_LIST}}

1. `tasks/backlog/` — planned, not yet started.
2. `tasks/active/` — in progress or blocked.
3. `tasks/done/` — completed, with completion metadata (a `YYYY-MM-DD` date and a
   PR/commit reference).

Base new task files on `tasks/templates/`. Do not keep long-lived planning
checklists at the repository root once the work belongs in this structure.

## Task id prefixes

Ids look like `{{TASK_ID_EXAMPLE}}` and use a registered prefix:

{{TASK_PREFIXES_BLOCK}}

Adjust this list in `agentkit.toml` (`[tasks].id_prefixes`).

## Required shape

All task files follow [task-format](/{{DOCS_AGENT_DIR}}/task-format.md): Goal,
Non-goals, Context, Required changes, Tests, Docs, Acceptance criteria,
Verification, Forbidden changes.

## Conventions

- Keep each task small and scoped.
- Use checkbox todos (`- [ ]`) in Required changes / Tests / Docs / Acceptance criteria.
- Create a task by copying a template, then editing its `# <ID> — <title>` heading:
  `cp tasks/templates/task.md tasks/backlog/{{TASK_ID_EXAMPLE}}-short-title.md`
  (or, if agentkit is installed: `agentkit new-task {{TASK_ID_EXAMPLE}} "Title"`)
- Validate with: `python3 {{CHECKS_DIR}}/check_tasks.py --root . --strict`
